<item>
            <title>[HIVE-4802] Fix url check for missing &quot;/&quot; or &quot;/&lt;db&gt; after hostname in jdb uri</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HIVE-4802</link>
                <project id="12310843" key="HIVE">Hive</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HIVE-4406&quot; title=&quot;Missing &amp;quot;/&amp;quot; or &amp;quot;/&amp;lt;dbname&amp;gt;&amp;quot; in hs2 jdbc uri switches mode to embedded mode&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HIVE-4406&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HIVE-4406&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; added a check for jdbc uri to prevent unintentional use of embedded mode. But that does not correctly check for uri like &quot;jdbc:hive2://localhost:10000;principal=hive/HiveServer2Host@YOUR-REALM.COM&quot; that can also result in embedded mode being used.&lt;/p&gt;

</description>
                <environment></environment>
